00:00:10.880 --> 00:00:13.120
A major obstacle to self-knowledge and in
turn, to a flourishing life, is our tendency

00:00:13.120 --> 00:00:15.040
to lie to ourselves.

00:00:18.880 --> 00:00:27.840
We lie for a very understandable
reason: because we want to avoid pain.

00:00:32.960 --> 00:00:36.800
There are four things we particularly like to lie
to ourselves about: Things we need to change

00:00:36.800 --> 00:00:39.680
about our lives. Things that might disturb
our self-image. Things we badly want and can't

00:00:39.680 --> 00:00:44.080
have. Things we are angry with orthers about
but don't dare to express. Here are some of the leading manoeuvers we employ to kid ourselves.

00:00:44.960 --> 00:00:47.040
1. Addiction.

00:00:49.600 --> 00:00:53.120
*Pornography noises*

00:01:02.080 --> 00:01:05.600
We identify something that can powerfully keep our thoughts
away from troubling inner confrontations.

00:01:12.640 --> 00:01:17.760
Often, we don't so much like what distracts
us in and of itself: we get attached because

00:01:18.720 --> 00:01:25.120
of its ability to keep us away from what we
fear.

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:28.480
2. Manic Cheeriness.

00:01:29.600 --> 00:01:36.080
Guys I just want to propse a toast to friendship and yeah just to having great times together. I'm so glad

00:01:36.080 --> 00:01:39.360
you came, I hope your all having fun.

00:01:39.360 --> 00:01:43.280
A sadness we haven't been able to admit to is often covered up withexaggerated doses of manic cheeriness.

00:01:45.440 --> 00:01:48.800
Are you having fun? Yeah Yeah.

00:01:48.960 --> 00:01:55.351
I'm so happy, it's so nice to see you. Yeah
you too. It's really lovely, it's really fun

00:01:55.360 --> 00:01:57.520
it's been really fun.You look amazing.

00:01:58.240 --> 00:02:04.720
We aren't happy so much as incapable of allowing ourselves to feel even the slightest sadness, in case we were to be overwhelmed by our troubling feelings.

00:02:06.160 --> 00:02:08.160
3. Denigration.

00:02:08.720 --> 00:02:12.400
I'm pleased I didn't go to university. I know you met alot of people

00:02:12.480 --> 00:02:18.080
and that you're friends for life but I don't
think that paying 9000 a year to make friends

00:02:18.080 --> 00:02:21.600
is really the best use of my money. Especially if i'm going to have to pay that back.

00:02:22.560 --> 00:02:26.781
We tell ourselves that we simply don't care about something - not because that's true, but because we can't have it.

00:02:27.440 --> 00:02:30.230
I have got a friend that
does contempary movement practise. I learnt

